        "_id": 6514,
        "Name": "Road to Comets",
        "Desc": "When <color style='color:#f29e38;'>Ice</color> or <color style='color:#f29e38;'>Imaginary</color> characters trigger the Weakness Break effect, additionally delay the enemy target's action by 50% and the DMG it receives increases by 50%, lasting until they recover from Weakness Break",
        "Story": "A gravitational bridge built through projections on spacial structures, judged by the Intelligentsia Guild as one of the ten thousand most useless inventions in the universe. This device was born from a gamble made by the History Fictionologist \"Red-Nosed Old-Timer.\" He claimed to be able to climb into the sky via lamplight and bet one-tenth of his wealth on it. However, when the distance is too long, walking on the light bridge is no different to a long-distance marathon. Yet if the distance is too short, the energy consumption needed to maintain the project far exceeds the cost of building a physical bridge — This is indeed an innovative creation, but it's hard to figure out where it should be used.",
